info.senderName: NWS GreenBay (East Central Wisconsin - Green Bay)
info.headline: Wind Advisory issued October 17 at 9:59PM CDT until October 18 at 1:00AM CDT by NWS GreenBay
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1 AM CDT TUESDAY... ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 1 AM TO 4 PM CDT TUESDAY... * WHAT...For the Wind Advisory, northwest winds 25 to 30 mph with gusts up to 45 mph. For the High Wind Warning, northwest winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 55 mph expected. * WHERE...Door County. * WHEN...For the Wind Advisory, until 1 AM CDT Tuesday. For the High Wind Warning, from 1 AM to 4 PM CDT Tuesday. * IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down trees and power lines. Widespread power outages are possible. Travel will be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
info.instruction: Winds this strong can make driving difficult, especially for high profile vehicles. Use extra caution. Secure outdoor objects.
